The paper deals with representing sets in a data structure and computing expressions involving unions and intersections of sets, which are fundamental operations in data structures and algorithms. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also mentions applications in information retrieval and database systems, which suggests cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.DB (Databases) as likely categories. The paper uses word-level parallelism, which is a common technique in parallel computing, suggesting cs.CC (Computational Complexity) as a possible category. Finally, the paper deals with the intersection of sets, which is a topic in discrete mathematics, suggesting cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) as a possible category.
